**Segments**

- On the basis of drug type, the rheumatology therapeutics market can be segmented into Disease Modifying Anti-Rheumatic Drugs (DMARDs), Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs), Corticosteroids, Uric Acid Drugs, and Others. DMARDs hold a significant share in the market, owing to their effectiveness in managing symptoms and slowing disease progression in rheumatoid arthritis and other autoimmune diseases.

- By disease type, the market is categorized into Rheumatoid Arthritis, Osteoarthritis, Psoriatic Arthritis, Ankylosing Spondylitis, and Others. Rheumatoid arthritis dominates the market due to the high prevalence of the disease globally and the increasing demand for advanced treatment options to alleviate symptoms and improve patients' quality of life.

- Based on distribution channel, the market is divided into Hospital Pharmacies, Retail Pharmacies, Online Pharmacies, and Others. Hospital pharmacies account for a significant market share as they are the primary source of dispensing prescription medications for rheumatologic conditions and provide convenient access to patients undergoing treatment.

